abstract: EAST AFRICA. -- From a European standpoint, Dr. Meyer declares the commercial value of the products of Kilimanjaro to be so far -- nil. abstract: AMHERST, March 7. -- Final preparations are being made for the Western tour of the Glee and Banjo Clubs at Easter in a special car. abstract: TORONTO, Ontario, March 7. -- There is still considerable diversity of opinion as to the actual majority the Government obtained in the recent elections. The Mail (independent) places the Government majority at 29, with Cariboo, Algoma, and Huntingdon to hear from. The World (Conservative) places the Government majority at 35, while 27 is the most the Globe (Liberal) can make it. Impartial authorities place the Government's majority at about 30.

It was a hard-fought battle and every inch of ground was closely contested by the bulldozing and unscrupulous opponents of the Australian system. A strong lobby had been at work against the bill from the day the session began -- probably the most influential that has ever been seen in Augusta.

abstract: CHICAGO, March 30. -- Fresh complications have risen to prevent an immediate settlement of the trouble caused by the cutting of passenger rates between St. Louis and Chicago by scalpers handling the tickets of the Jacksonville Southeastern Road. A meeting was held at Chairman Finley's office to-day by representatives of all the lines in interest to hear the report of the Chairman on the situation.
